the 2028 Summer Games\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 252}, {\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 280}, {\"ngram\": \"Sept.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"City Hall\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 303}, {\"ngram\": \"the return\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 327}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flag\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"Angels\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 369}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"the arrival\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 200 people - including over 40 former Olympians and Paralympians who participated in games as long ago as 1968 - attended to celebrate Los Angeles as host of the next Summer Games.\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999943157, \"rank\": 5.643266365174902e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More than 200 people\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"over 40 former Olympians\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 493}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympians\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"games\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"host\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"the next Summer Games\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2028, L.A. will host theOlympics for the third timeand the Paralympics for the first time.\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.0128148801572756e-13, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc