ing it during theParalympics closing ceremonyheld on Sunday.\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 987, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.0128148801572756e-13, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theParalympics closing ceremonyheld\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today, as we take responsibility for these flags here in Los Angeles and for the next four years, we take on the responsibility of lifting up the values of the Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999943157, \"rank\": 5.643266365174902e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"responsibility\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"these flags\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"the next four years\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"the responsibility\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is in that spirit that we believe the 2028 Olympic and Paralympic Games in Los Angeles will be a 'Games for All,'\\\" Bass said in a speech during Thursday's flag installation ceremony.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999943157, \"rank\": 5.643266365174902e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bass_guitar\", \"score\": 0.9999617316456076, \"rank\": 3.826975911664839e-05, \"text\": \"Bass\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bass_guitar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bass_guitar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that spirit\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympic and Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'Games\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"a speech\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday's flag installation ceremony\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With \\\"Games for All\\\" as the theme of Thursday's ceremony, Bass said she wants an Olympics that benefits all Angelenos - from supporting local small businesses and stimulating the economy to making lasting improvements to the environment and the region's mass transportation system.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1515, \"end\": 1519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bass_guitar\", \"score\": 0.9999617316456076, \"rank\": 3.826975911664839e-05, \"text\": \"Bass\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bass_guitar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bass_guitar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Games\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1468}, {\"ngram\": \"the theme\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday's ceremony\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"all Angelenos\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"local small businesses\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"the economy\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"lasting improvements\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1674}, {\"ngram\": \"the environment\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"the region's mass transportation system\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We want to live up to that declaration so that all Angelenos in every corner of our city benefit from the major global event - not just during the summer of 2028 but starting now and for decades to come,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that declaration\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"all Angelenos\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"every corner\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1817}, {\"ngram\": \"our city benefit\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1837}, {\"ngram\": \"the major global event\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1865}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1894}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thursday's ceremony began with a taiko drum performance by the J-Town Taiko Club in Los Angeles, a land welcoming by Chief Anthony Morales of the Gabrieleno-San Gabriel Band of Mission Indians, and a performance by members of Inner City Youth Orchestra, the largest majority-Black orchestra in America.\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.522643890204123e-16, \"text\": \"Taiko\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiko\"}, {\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999943157, \"rank\": 5.64326636517